{"id":14881801,"mediaExerciseId":"d12810eb-9635-498f-9ee6-5fc8429f79dd","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"22","chapterTitle":"Behavioral Finance: Implications For Financial Management","groupId":612479,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":761,"solutions":[{"id":5673648,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this question, we are asked to determine the noise trader risk and its influence on market inefficiencies.\n\n\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":61,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/22/0f658e1633382e635a384d5fbec0d9c5/be78d8ff3b482e30260d0aa736077995/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/22/0f658e1633382e635a384d5fbec0d9c5/be78d8ff3b482e30260d0aa736077995/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"First, let's understand what behavioral finance and market efficiency is.\n\nBehavioral finance aims to understand why and how an Individual's financial or investment decisions extensively influence the market. Understanding these patternsÂ can help people create sensible judgments in trading or investing. The noise trading risk is one of the investment risks tackled in this study.\n\nMarket efficiency is when a market is timely and accurately reflects an asset's actual value and displays relevant information. Market efficiency is deeply associated with behavioral finance since this is the primary goal of the study.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":291,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/22/0f658e1633382e635a384d5fbec0d9c5/4e7981ec1d33f822018a9e0618ea7508/lateximg_large.png","width":1019},"regular":{"height":147,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/22/0f658e1633382e635a384d5fbec0d9c5/4e7981ec1d33f822018a9e0618ea7508/lateximg.png","width":509}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Next, let us now define the noise trading risk.\n\n**Noise trading risk** is a risk associated with the possibility of traders making misinformed decisions due to an excess of noise in the market created by noise traders. Noise traders make decisions based on the latest trend without any fundamental or technical analysis of the asset.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":179,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/18/0f658e1633382e635a384d5fbec0d9c5/514a15308aa69236462c41ddfce32ca1/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":91,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/18/0f658e1633382e635a384d5fbec0d9c5/514a15308aa69236462c41ddfce32ca1/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"For the second requirement, to understand how noise traders' risk influences market inefficiencies, let's know what market inefficiency is.\n\nMarket inefficiency, or can also be called market failure, is the circumstance when a price of an asset on the market is not accurate or no longer corresponds with its actual value.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":173,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/12/0f658e1633382e635a384d5fbec0d9c5/7ee6f246ac06bfb74fccec16b07d1aa5/lateximg_large.png","width":1008},"regular":{"height":88,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/12/0f658e1633382e635a384d5fbec0d9c5/7ee6f246ac06bfb74fccec16b07d1aa5/lateximg.png","width":503}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Finally, let's now understand how noise trader risk influences market inefficiency.\n\n**Noise trader risk can cause market inefficiency** due to a large number of noise traders can significantly influence a value of an asset by mispricing them, leading to higher volatility and creating more noise in the market to attract investors.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":174,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/12/0f658e1633382e635a384d5fbec0d9c5/95fb1788d9c38c426f9d4da2728f1a3a/lateximg_large.png","width":1041},"regular":{"height":89,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/11/12/0f658e1633382e635a384d5fbec0d9c5/95fb1788d9c38c426f9d4da2728f1a3a/lateximg.png","width":520}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"6db16a12-16f6-41f3-be61-8a15d47031e4","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881802,"exerciseName":"5","page":761,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"6b973c08-2db5-4030-b205-2d18e6a17ef5","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-22-critical-thinking-questions-5-6b973c08-2db5-4030-b205-2d18e6a17ef5"},{"id":14881803,"exerciseName":"6","page":762,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"472f8f09-b99e-443a-a03f-12595273d96d","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-22-critical-thinkin